---
title: Belgian Waffles with Maple-Pear Compote plus Cranberry-Almond Yogurt Parfaits
description: If you love the way the crisp pockets of toasted Belgian waffles (the thick, fluffy kind!) hold onto syrup and other toppings, you’re in for a treat. You’ll top these waffles with homemade pear-cinnamon-maple compote swirled with butter and fresh lemon juice. Round out your morning meal with a creamy maple yogurt parfait sprinkled with nutty almonds and chewy-sweet dried cranberries, and you’re all but guaranteed to have a great rest of your day.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65de532a565f56a1bd212702-b6b60436.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65de532a565f56a1bd212702.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 96 g
  sugar: 65 g
  protein: 9 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 430 mg
course: main course
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/belgian-waffles-with-maple-pear-compote-65de532a565f56a1bd212702
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and dice @pear{1} into ½-inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add pear, @cinnamon{1%tsp}, @brown sugar{1%tbsp}, half the @maple syrup{2%tbsp}, ¼ cup water, juice from one lemon wedge, and a @salt{pinch} (½ cup water and juice from two wedges for 4). (Save remaining lemon wedges for another use.)

Bring mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pear is softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Gently mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mixture is soft but still chunky.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @yogurt{1/2%cup}, @crème fraîche{4%tbsp}, and remaining maple syrup.

Toast @Belgian waffle{2} in a #toaster{} until golden brown.

Divide yogurt mixture between two small #serving cups{} or #bowls{} (four cups or bowls for 4 servings). Garnish with @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and @dried cranberries{1%oz}.

Divide waffles between #plates{}; top with pear compote. Serve with parfaits on the side.

> Round out your morning meal with a creamy maple yogurt parfait sprinkled with nutty almonds and chewy-sweet dried cranberries.